messages.message: This one is super cool, if you guys haven't played with it: https://github.com/OthersideAI/self-operating-computer  -- this can actually make RPA fully irrelevant with some sort of Central Controller and a set of Local Worker Agents [each running on the desktops]. It's not fully reliable yet, still makes a lot of errors, but I think it will soon get there. The reason why I believe that is because there is ton more training data available in the world for GUIs, and GUIs donâ€™t require the same formal correctness as UIs [HTML parsing]/APIs.
